com.bmd.jrt.builder

Interface RoutineChannelBuilder

  • All Superinterfaces:
    RoutineBuilder
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    InvocationRoutineBuilder, RoutineConfigurationBuilder

    public interface RoutineChannelBuilder
extends RoutineBuilder
    Interface extending a builder of routine objects.

    In addition to a routine builder, the number of input and output data buffered in the corresponding channel can be limited in order to avoid excessive memory consumption. In case the maximum number is reached when passing an input or output, the call blocks until enough data are consumed or the specified timeout elapses. In the latter case a DeadLockException will be thrown.

    Finally, by default the order of input and output data is not guaranteed. Nevertheless, it is possible to force data to be delivered in insertion order, at the cost of a slightly increased memory usage and computation, by calling the proper methods.

    Created by davide on 11/11/14.
